by nicolas-grekas at 2015-10-27T15:28:55Z

`composer validate` is now used to display a detailed error message in case an invalid composer.json file is found. E.g.:
```
  "src/Symfony/Component/HttpKernel//composer.json" does not contain valid JSON
  Parse error on line 37:
  ...ating": "~2.2",    },    "suggest": {
  ---------------------^
  Expected: 'STRING' - It appears you have an extra trailing comma
```

